claim: Vaccination with a higher-dose recombinant flu vaccine may induce a more robust antibody response than egg-based standard-dose vaccines.
explanation: A flowchart for determining the number of 2022–23 influenza vaccine doses for children based on whether they received ≥2 doses of trivalent or quadrivalent influenza vaccine before July 1, 2022. If yes, administer 1 dose of 2022–23 vaccine; if no or unknown, administer 2 doses at least 4 weeks apart. does not support the claim because the figure only outlines dose scheduling for pediatric influenza vaccination and provides no data on antibody responses or comparisons between higher-dose recombinant and egg-based standard-dose vaccines.
